POSSIBLE ERRORS

P1-
PERMISSION_DENIED
403 Forbidden
Path does not exist
Cannot access abfss/s3 path

Databricks cluster/job does not have permission to read or write to schema_location,checkpoint_location,target_table

P2-
useManagedFileEvents not supported or not configured properly-.option("cloudFiles.useManagedFileEvents", "true")

P3-
Schema location issue
Issues happen when:
Path is not writable
Same schema location is reused by another pipeline
Old schema metadata conflicts with new source files
Path accidentally deleted

Solution
Use a dedicated schema location per source/table.

P4-
Checkpoint location issue
Failures happen if:
Checkpoint deleted
Checkpoint reused for another table
Code changed drastically
Multiple jobs use same checkpoint
Manual modification happened

Solution
Use one checkpoint per streaming query.

P5-
Schema evolution failure
In real projects, better to define schema manually.
Use schema evolution mode-.option("cloudFiles.schemaEvolutionMode", "addNewColumns")

P6-
Duplicate processing or duplicate rows
Why it can happen
Auto Loader gives strong file-level tracking using checkpoint, but duplicates can still happen if:

Same data comes in different file names
Checkpoint is deleted
Job reruns with a new checkpoint
Upstream sends duplicate files
Same source path is processed by two pipe

->Add metadata columns:current_filestamp(),input_file_name()


P7-
If you are using Auto Loader with cloudFiles.schemaEvolutionMode = "addNewColumns", then when a new column arrives, Auto Loader may fail the stream once with an UnknownFieldException. Before failing, it updates the schema in the configured cloudFiles.schemaLocation. After restart/retry, the stream can continue with the updated schema. [docs.databricks.com], [community....bricks.com]

So in a Job/Workflow, adding retry to the ingest task is a good practice.




